---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Consulting — Tim Raysby"
  description="Selective consulting on production-grade agentic AI systems. Currently considering 1-2 engagements per quarter."
  wide
>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════ HERO ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="pt-4 pb-20 md:pb-24">
    <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2.5 px-4 py-2 border border-green bg-green/10 font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-green mb-8">
      <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-green rounded-full animate-pulse"></span>
      Selective &middot; 1&ndash;2 engagements per quarter
    </div>
    <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-normal leading-none tracking-tight mb-8 max-w-4xl">
      Production-grade <em class="italic text-green font-normal">Agent Stacks</em> for operators ready to ship.
    </h1>
    <p class="max-w-2xl text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink mb-10">
      Most AI projects demo well and die in production. I help technical teams move
      agentic AI from prototype to enterprise reality &mdash; designing the agent workflows,
      building the cloud infrastructure they run on, and orchestrating the pieces so the
      system actually works under real load.
    </p>
    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-6 sm:gap-12 text-xs text-ink-dim uppercase tracking-wider font-mono pt-6 border-t border-charcoal-lighter">
      <div>
        <span>Current availability</span>
        <span class="block mt-1.5 text-ink font-medium text-[13px] normal-case tracking-normal">
          Notify-only &middot; evaluating fit on a per-engagement basis
        </span>
      </div>
      <div>
        <span>Best fits</span>
        <span class="block mt-1.5 text-ink font-medium text-[13px] normal-case tracking-normal">
          Technical buyers with production AI needs
        </span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════ THE SERVICE ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="py-20 md:py-24 border-t border-charcoal-lighter">
    <p class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-green mb-5 flex items-center gap-3">
      <span class="w-7 h-px bg-green"></span>
      The Service
    </p>
    <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl font-normal leading-tight tracking-tight mb-8 max-w-3xl">
      An <em class="italic text-green font-normal">Agent Stack</em> is the layered system that turns generic LLMs into a working part of your business.
    </h2>
    <p class="text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink max-w-3xl mb-4">
      Most "AI consulting" today is a demo wrapper around an API key. An Agent Stack
      is different &mdash; it's the production infrastructure, agent orchestration, and
      business-specific knowledge integration that determines whether your AI runs at
      2 a.m. on a Sunday, or fails silently when it matters.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-14 border-t border-charcoal-lighter">

      <!-- Layer 01 -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[200px_1fr] gap-4 md:gap-12 py-10 border-b border-charcoal-lighter">
        <div class="font-mono text-xs tracking-wider text-green uppercase pt-2">
          <span class="block font-serif text-5xl md:text-6xl text-charcoal-lighter mb-3 font-light leading-none">01</span>
          Foundation Layer
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl font-medium leading-tight mb-4">
            Cloud infrastructure that doesn't fall over.
          </h3>
          <p class="text-ink-dim text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
            Hosting, observability, secrets management, networking, identity, cost controls.
            The boring foundation that determines whether your agent system is production
            software or a science project. Built on infrastructure you own and operate
            &mdash; no vendor lock-in.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-5">
            <span class="font-mono text-[11px] px-2.5 py-1 bg-charcoal-light text-ink-dim border border-charcoal-lighter">Infrastructure-as-code</span>
            <span class="font-mono text-[11px] px-2.5 py-1 bg-charcoal-light text-ink-dim border border-charcoal-lighter">Observability</span>
            <span class="font-mono text-[11px] px-2.5 py-1 bg-charcoal-light text-ink-dim border border-charcoal-lighter">Cost controls</span>
            <span class="font-mono text-[11px] px-2.5 py-1 bg-charcoal-light text-ink-dim border border-charcoal-lighter">Self-hosted-ready</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Layer 02 -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[200px_1fr] gap-4 md:gap-12 py-10 border-b border-charcoal-lighter">
        <div class="font-mono text-xs tracking-wider text-green uppercase pt-2">
          <span class="block font-serif text-5xl md:text-6xl text-charcoal-lighter mb-3 font-light leading-none">02</span>
          Agent Layer
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl font-medium leading-tight mb-4">
            Multi-model orchestration that handles real edge cases.
          </h3>
          <p class="text-ink-dim text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
            Reasoning loops, tool calling, multi-agent coordination, model routing between
            local and frontier providers, retry logic, error handling. The difference
            between an agent that demos in a sandbox and one that operates against real
            data with real consequences.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-5">
            <span class="font-mono text-[11px] px-2.5 py-1 bg-charcoal-light text-ink-dim border border-charcoal-lighter">Multi-agent orchestration</span>
            <span class="font-mono text-[11px] px-2.5 py-1 bg-charcoal-light text-ink-dim border border-charcoal-lighter">Tool integration</span>
            <span class="font-mono text-[11px] px-2.5 py-1 bg-charcoal-light text-ink-dim border border-charcoal-lighter">Model routing</span>
            <span class="font-mono text-[11px] px-2.5 py-1 bg-charcoal-light text-ink-dim border border-charcoal-lighter">Failure handling</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Layer 03 -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[200px_1fr] gap-4 md:gap-12 py-10 border-b border-charcoal-lighter">
        <div class="font-mono text-xs tracking-wider text-green uppercase pt-2">
          <span class="block font-serif text-5xl md:text-6xl text-charcoal-lighter mb-3 font-light leading-none">03</span>
          Knowledge Layer
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl font-medium leading-tight mb-4">
            The business context that makes generic AI yours.
          </h3>
          <p class="text-ink-dim text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
            Retrieval strategy, document pipelines, vector stores, the institutional
            knowledge that turns a clever model into a system that understands your
            specific operation. Where the engagement moves from infrastructure work into
            actually solving your problem.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-5">
            <span class="font-mono text-[11px] px-2.5 py-1 bg-charcoal-light text-ink-dim border border-charcoal-lighter">Retrieval architectures</span>
            <span class="font-mono text-[11px] px-2.5 py-1 bg-charcoal-light text-ink-dim border border-charcoal-lighter">Document pipelines</span>
            <span class="font-mono text-[11px] px-2.5 py-1 bg-charcoal-light text-ink-dim border border-charcoal-lighter">Domain ontologies</span>
            <span class="font-mono text-[11px] px-2.5 py-1 bg-charcoal-light text-ink-dim border border-charcoal-lighter">Pattern reuse</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════ PRINCIPLES ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="py-20 md:py-24 border-t border-charcoal-lighter">
    <p class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-green mb-5 flex items-center gap-3">
      <span class="w-7 h-px bg-green"></span>
      How I Think About This
    </p>
    <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl font-normal leading-tight tracking-tight mb-2 max-w-3xl">
      Three principles that <em class="italic text-green font-normal">shape every engagement</em>.
    </h2>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 md:gap-8 mt-12">
      <article class="p-8 bg-charcoal-light border border-charcoal-lighter hover:border-green transition-colors">
        <div class="font-mono text-[11px] text-green tracking-widest mb-4">[ 01 ]</div>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl md:text-2xl font-medium leading-snug mb-3">Solve once. Reuse forever.</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-dim text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Every pattern shipped in an engagement becomes part of a reusable corpus &mdash;
          not throwaway prototype code. The architecture compounds across projects instead
          of restarting every time. Long-term clients benefit from work done for earlier ones.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="p-8 bg-charcoal-light border border-charcoal-lighter hover:border-green transition-colors">
        <div class="font-mono text-[11px] text-green tracking-widest mb-4">[ 02 ]</div>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl md:text-2xl font-medium leading-snug mb-3">Ownership over convenience.</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-dim text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Your AI stack should run on infrastructure you own. No critical workflows locked
          behind a third-party API that can deprecate, rate-limit, or change pricing without
          notice. Self-hosted where it matters; managed services only where the trade-off
          makes sense.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="p-8 bg-charcoal-light border border-charcoal-lighter hover:border-green transition-colors">
        <div class="font-mono text-[11px] text-green tracking-widest mb-4">[ 03 ]</div>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl md:text-2xl font-medium leading-snug mb-3">Production beats demo, always.</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-dim text-sm leading-relaxed">
          The interesting work in agentic AI isn't getting a happy-path demo to work. It's
          the edge cases, the failure modes, the 2 a.m. alerts, the silent regressions.
          Engineering discipline applied to AI systems, not AI enthusiasm dressed up as
          engineering.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════ REFERENCE BUILD (SANITIZED) ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="py-20 md:py-24 border-t border-charcoal-lighter">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 md:gap-16 items-start">

      <div>
        <p class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-green mb-5 flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="w-7 h-px bg-green"></span>
          Reference Build
        </p>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-normal leading-tight tracking-tight mb-6">
          I run the <em class="italic text-green font-normal">same architecture</em> on my own work first.
        </h2>
        <p class="text-ink text-base leading-relaxed mb-5">
          Before recommending an Agent Stack to anyone, I'm running one on my own
          operation. Multi-agent orchestration, pattern reuse, local-first model
          routing &mdash; the full architecture applied to my own work as the reference
          implementation behind the consulting.
        </p>
        <p class="text-ink-dim text-sm leading-relaxed">
          It's the proof the patterns work in real conditions, not just slides. The same
          architecture gets applied to client engagements with their specific knowledge
          layer.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="relative bg-charcoal-light border border-green p-8 md:p-10 mt-2">
        <span class="absolute -top-2 left-6 bg-charcoal px-3 font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.25em] text-green">// REFERENCE BUILD</span>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl font-normal text-green tracking-tight mb-3">Production runtime</h3>
        <p class="font-mono text-xs text-ink-dim italic mb-5">// proof it ships, not what it ships on</p>
        <p class="text-ink text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Scheduled jobs firing on time every day. Content publishing autonomously across
          multiple platforms. Voice capture, transcription, and content generation running
          on operator-owned hardware.
        </p>
        <p class="text-ink text-sm leading-relaxed mb-5">
          No cloud-LLM dependency in the production path. Failures are boring &mdash; logged,
          retried, surfaced for review. Operator data stays on operator hardware.
        </p>
        <div class="font-mono text-[11px] leading-loose text-ink-dim mt-6 pt-5 border-t border-charcoal-lighter">
          <div><span class="text-green">runtime:</span> 24/7, autonomous, self-healing</div>
          <div><span class="text-green">deploy boundary:</span> operator-owned hardware</div>
          <div><span class="text-green">vendor surface:</span> minimized by design</div>
          <div><span class="text-green">status:</span> shipping in production</div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════ FIT QUALIFIER ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="py-20 md:py-24 border-t border-charcoal-lighter">
    <p class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-green mb-5 flex items-center gap-3">
      <span class="w-7 h-px bg-green"></span>
      Engagement Fit
    </p>
    <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl font-normal leading-tight tracking-tight mb-2 max-w-3xl">
      Not every problem is a fit. <em class="italic text-green font-normal">Be honest with yourself</em> before reaching out.
    </h2>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 md:gap-8 mt-14">
      <div class="p-8 bg-charcoal-light border border-green">
        <h4 class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-widest uppercase text-green mb-5">+ Good fit</h4>
        <ul class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
          <li class="text-ink py-2.5 pl-7 relative border-b border-dashed border-charcoal-lighter before:content-['+'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-green before:font-bold before:font-mono">You have a real production AI need, not a "we should explore AI" mandate</li>
          <li class="text-ink py-2.5 pl-7 relative border-b border-dashed border-charcoal-lighter before:content-['+'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-green before:font-bold before:font-mono">You're a technical buyer or have a technical lead in the loop</li>
          <li class="text-ink py-2.5 pl-7 relative border-b border-dashed border-charcoal-lighter before:content-['+'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-green before:font-bold before:font-mono">You have budget for engineering work, not hackathon pricing</li>
          <li class="text-ink py-2.5 pl-7 relative border-b border-dashed border-charcoal-lighter before:content-['+'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-green before:font-bold before:font-mono">You want to own your infrastructure, not be locked into a vendor</li>
          <li class="text-ink py-2.5 pl-7 relative border-b border-dashed border-charcoal-lighter before:content-['+'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-green before:font-bold before:font-mono">You've already tried something with AI and hit a real limitation</li>
          <li class="text-ink py-2.5 pl-7 relative before:content-['+'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-green before:font-bold before:font-mono">You can articulate the specific function you want agents to handle</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="p-8 bg-charcoal-light border border-charcoal-lighter">
        <h4 class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-widest uppercase text-ink-dimmer mb-5">&minus; Not a fit (right now)</h4>
        <ul class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
          <li class="text-ink-dim py-2.5 pl-7 relative border-b border-dashed border-charcoal-lighter before:content-['\2212'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-ink-dimmer before:font-bold before:font-mono">You need someone urgently &mdash; I have a day role and limited capacity</li>
          <li class="text-ink-dim py-2.5 pl-7 relative border-b border-dashed border-charcoal-lighter before:content-['\2212'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-ink-dimmer before:font-bold before:font-mono">You want a vendor-managed SaaS solution rather than owned infrastructure</li>
          <li class="text-ink-dim py-2.5 pl-7 relative border-b border-dashed border-charcoal-lighter before:content-['\2212'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-ink-dimmer before:font-bold before:font-mono">Your goal is "explore AI" without a defined business outcome</li>
          <li class="text-ink-dim py-2.5 pl-7 relative border-b border-dashed border-charcoal-lighter before:content-['\2212'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-ink-dimmer before:font-bold before:font-mono">You need a turnkey product, not custom engineering</li>
          <li class="text-ink-dim py-2.5 pl-7 relative border-b border-dashed border-charcoal-lighter before:content-['\2212'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-ink-dimmer before:font-bold before:font-mono">You're shopping ChatGPT wrappers and want the cheapest option</li>
          <li class="text-ink-dim py-2.5 pl-7 relative before:content-['\2212'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-ink-dimmer before:font-bold before:font-mono">You can't articulate what success looks like beyond "use AI"</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════ NOTIFY / CONTACT ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section id="notify" class="py-20 md:py-24 border-t border-charcoal-lighter">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <p class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-green mb-5 flex items-center gap-3">
        <span class="w-7 h-px bg-green"></span>
        Get Notified
      </p>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl font-normal leading-tight tracking-tight mb-2">
        Currently <em class="italic text-green font-normal">fully booked</em>.
      </h2>

      <div class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-dim mt-10 mb-10 p-5 bg-charcoal-light border-l-[3px] border-green">
        <p>
          <strong class="text-green font-medium">Honest status:</strong> I architect agentic
          AI systems at a major insurer during the day and build the reference stack in the
          evenings. I take on <strong class="text-ink font-medium">1&ndash;2 external engagements per quarter</strong>,
          evaluated on fit.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The notify list is how I let prospective fits know when capacity opens up. Tell
          me what you're trying to ship &mdash; if it's a good match, I'll reach out when the
          timing works on both sides.
        </p>
      </div>

      <form
        id="consulting-waitlist-form"
        action="/api/consulting-waitlist"
        method="post"
        novalidate
        class="grid gap-4"
      >
        <div>
          <label for="cw-name" class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-widest uppercase text-ink-dim mb-2 block">Name</label>
          <input
            id="cw-name"
            type="text"
            name="name"
            required
            maxlength="100"
            autocomplete="name"
            class="w-full bg-charcoal-light border border-charcoal-lighter px-4 py-3 text-ink font-mono text-sm focus:outline-none focus:border-green transition-colors"
          />
        </div>
        <div>
          <label for="cw-email" class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-widest uppercase text-ink-dim mb-2 block">Email</label>
          <input
            id="cw-email"
            type="email"
            name="email"
            required
            autocomplete="email"
            class="w-full bg-charcoal-light border border-charcoal-lighter px-4 py-3 text-ink font-mono text-sm focus:outline-none focus:border-green transition-colors"
          />
        </div>
        <div>
          <label for="cw-company" class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-widest uppercase text-ink-dim mb-2 block">Company / Role (optional)</label>
          <input
            id="cw-company"
            type="text"
            name="company"
            maxlength="200"
            autocomplete="organization"
            class="w-full bg-charcoal-light border border-charcoal-lighter px-4 py-3 text-ink font-mono text-sm focus:outline-none focus:border-green transition-colors"
          />
        </div>
        <div>
          <label for="cw-problem" class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-widest uppercase text-ink-dim mb-2 block">What are you trying to ship?</label>
          <textarea
            id="cw-problem"
            name="problem"
            required
            maxlength="5000"
            rows="5"
            placeholder="The specific business function or technical problem you'd want an Agent Stack to solve. Be concrete."
            class="w-full bg-charcoal-light border border-charcoal-lighter px-4 py-3 text-ink font-mono text-sm focus:outline-none focus:border-green transition-colors resize-y min-h-[120px] leading-relaxed"
          ></textarea>
        </div>
        <button
          type="submit"
          id="consulting-waitlist-submit"
          class="mt-3 px-8 py-4 bg-green text-charcoal border border-green font-mono text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.18em] uppercase hover:bg-charcoal hover:text-green transition-colors justify-self-start disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed"
        >Get on the list &rarr;</button>
      </form>
      <p id="consulting-waitlist-result" class="mt-4 text-sm font-mono" aria-live="polite"></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script is:inline>
    (() => {
      const form = document.getElementById('consulting-waitlist-form');
      const submit = document.getElementById('consulting-waitlist-submit');
      const result = document.getElementById('consulting-waitlist-result');
      if (!form || !submit || !result) return;

      form.addEventListener('submit', async (ev) => {
        ev.preventDefault();
        const fd = new FormData(form);
        const payload = {
          name: String(fd.get('name') || '').trim(),
          email: String(fd.get('email') || '').trim(),
          company: String(fd.get('company') || '').trim(),
          problem: String(fd.get('problem') || '').trim(),
        };
        if (!payload.name) {
          result.textContent = 'Please enter your name.';
          result.className = 'mt-4 text-sm font-mono text-ink-dim';
          return;
        }
        if (!payload.email) {
          result.textContent = 'Please enter your email.';
          result.className = 'mt-4 text-sm font-mono text-ink-dim';
          return;
        }
        if (!payload.problem) {
          result.textContent = "Please tell me what you're trying to ship.";
          result.className = 'mt-4 text-sm font-mono text-ink-dim';
          return;
        }
        const originalText = submit.textContent;
        submit.disabled = true;
        submit.textContent = 'Submitting...';
        result.textContent = '';
        try {
          const resp = await fetch(form.action, {
            method: 'POST',
            headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
            body: JSON.stringify(payload),
          });
          let data = {};
          try { data = await resp.json(); } catch { /* ignore */ }
          if (resp.ok && data && data.ok) {
            result.textContent = "You're on the list. I'll reach out when a slot opens and the fit looks right.";
            result.className = 'mt-4 text-sm font-mono text-green';
            form.reset();
          } else {
            const msg = (data && data.error) || 'Submission failed. Please try again.';
            result.textContent = msg;
            result.className = 'mt-4 text-sm font-mono text-ink-dim';
          }
        } catch (e) {
          result.textContent = 'Could not reach the server. Please try again, or email contact@timraysby.com.';
          result.className = 'mt-4 text-sm font-mono text-ink-dim';
        } finally {
          submit.disabled = false;
          submit.textContent = originalText;
        }
      });
    })();
  </script>

</Layout>
